SIMPLE: instalment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: instalment
<hw>in*stal"ment</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of installing;
installation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take oaths from all kings and magistrates at their
<qex>installment</qex>, to do impartial justice by law.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The seat in which one is placed.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The several chairs of order, look, you scour; . . . ⟦br⟧
Each fair <qex>installment</qex>, coat, and several crest⟦br⟧
With loyal blazon, evermore be blest.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A portion of a debt, or sum of money, which is
divided into portions that are made payable at different times; that
portion of a debt payed back in any one payment; <as>as, the next
<ex>installment</ex> is due January first</as>. Payment by
<ex>installment</ex> is payment by parts at different times, the amounts
and times being often definitely stipulated.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a part of a broadcast serial.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> episode.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>a part of a published serial.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instamp</ent>⟦br⟧
